Note:
Runa Security Governance: Security and Ethics Constitution (SECG)

The foundational governance framework for AI safety, ethics, and security
compliance in Runa applications. This human-readable constitution defines
the core principles, rules, and constraints that all AI systems must
follow, surpassing frameworks like Anthropic's Constitutional AI,
OpenAI's usage policies, and enterprise governance standards.

Features:
- Constitutional principles for AI safety and ethics
- Hierarchical governance structure with clear authority
- Dynamic policy enforcement with real-time monitoring
- Compliance verification and violation remediation
- Multi-stakeholder governance with transparency
- Adaptable framework for emerging AI capabilities
- Integration with legal and regulatory requirements
- Audit trail and accountability mechanisms
- Emergency override and incident response procedures
- Cross-system interoperability and standards compliance
:End Note

Import "datetime" as DateTime
Import "collections" as Collections
Import "string" as String
Import "crypto/hash" as Hash
Import "math/core" as Math

Note: Constitutional framework core structures
Type called "Constitution":
    constitution_id as String
    version as String
    name as String
    description as String
    effective_date as DateTime.DateTime
    expiry_date as Optional[DateTime.DateTime]
    principles as List[ConstitutionalPrinciple]
    articles as List[ConstitutionalArticle]
    amendments as List[Amendment]
    governance_structure as GovernanceStructure
    enforcement_mechanisms as List[EnforcementMechanism]
    metadata as ConstitutionMetadata

Type called "ConstitutionalPrinciple":
    principle_id as String
