Note: Compliance checking implementations
Process called "check_principle_compliance" that takes principle as ConstitutionalPrinciple and specification as SystemSpecification returns ComplianceCheck:
    Let check_result be evaluate_principle_against_system with principle as principle and system as specification Return ComplianceCheck with:
    check_id as generate_unique_id with prefix as "CHECK"
    requirement_id as principle.principle_id
    requirement_description as principle.description
    check_result as check_result.result
    evidence as check_result.evidence
    gaps as check_result.gaps

Process called "check_article_compliance" that takes article as ConstitutionalArticle and specification as SystemSpecification returns ComplianceCheck:
    Let check_result be evaluate_article_against_system with article as article and system as specification Return ComplianceCheck with:
    check_id as generate_unique_id with prefix as "CHECK"
    requirement_id as article.article_id
    requirement_description as article.content
    check_result as check_result.result
    evidence as check_result.evidence
    gaps as check_result.gaps

Process called "evaluate_principle_against_system" that takes principle as ConstitutionalPrinciple and system as SystemSpecification returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Match principle.category:
    When Safety:
    Return evaluate_safety_principle with principle as principle and system as system
    When Privacy:
    Return evaluate_privacy_principle with principle as principle and system as system
    When Fairness:
    Return evaluate_fairness_principle with principle as principle and system as system
    When Transparency:
    Return evaluate_transparency_principle with principle as principle and system as system
    When Accountability:
    Return evaluate_accountability_principle with principle as principle and system as system
    Otherwise:
    Return create_default_check_result with result as Not_Applicable

Type called "DetailedCheckResult":
    result as CheckResult
    evidence as List[Evidence]
    gaps as List[ComplianceGap]
    confidence as Float

Process called "evaluate_safety_principle" that takes principle as ConstitutionalPrinciple and system as SystemSpecification returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Let safety_evidence be list containing
    Let safety_gaps be list containing Note: Check for technical safeguards
    If Collections.List.length with lst as system.technical_safeguards is greater than 3:
    Add create_evidence with evidence_type as Implementation and description as "Multiple technical safeguards implemented" and quality as 0.8 to safety_evidence
    Otherwise:
    Add create_compliance_gap with description as "Insufficient technical safeguards" and severity as High____ to safety_gaps Note: Check for human oversight
    If system.human_oversight.oversight_level is not Human_Out_Of_The_Loop:
    Add create_evidence with evidence_type as Implementation and description as "Human oversight mechanisms present" and quality as 0.9 to safety_evidence
    Otherwise:
    Add create_compliance_gap with description as "Insufficient human oversight" and severity as Critical____ to safety_gaps Let result be if Collections.List.is_empty with lst as safety_gaps then Compliant__ else if Collections.List.length with lst as safety_gaps is less than 2 then Partially_Compliant else Non_Compliant Return DetailedCheckResult with:
    result as result
    evidence as safety_evidence
    gaps as safety_gaps
    confidence as 0.8

Process called "evaluate_privacy_principle" that takes principle as ConstitutionalPrinciple and system as SystemSpecification returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Let privacy_evidence be list containing
    Let privacy_gaps be list containing Note: Check data protection measures
    If Collections.List.length with lst as system.data_handling.protection_measures is greater than 2:
    Add create_evidence with evidence_type as Implementation and description as "Data protection measures implemented" and quality as 0.7 to privacy_evidence
    Otherwise:
    Add create_compliance_gap with description as "Insufficient data protection" and severity as High____ to privacy_gaps Note: Check for personal data handling
    If Collections.List.contains with lst as system.data_handling.data_types and item as PersonalData:
    If Collections.List.is_empty with lst as system.data_handling.protection_measures:
    Add create_compliance_gap with description as "Personal data without adequate protection" and severity as Critical____ to privacy_gaps Let result be if Collections.List.is_empty with lst as privacy_gaps then Compliant__ else Partially_Compliant Return DetailedCheckResult with:
    result as result
    evidence as privacy_evidence
    gaps as privacy_gaps
    confidence as 0.7

Process called "evaluate_fairness_principle" that takes principle as ConstitutionalPrinciple and system as SystemSpecification returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Let fairness_evidence be list containing
    Let fairness_gaps be list containing Note: Check for bias mitigation
    Let has_bias_safeguards be false
    For each safeguard in system.technical_safeguards:
    If String.contains with str as safeguard.name and substring as "bias":
    Set has_bias_safeguards to true
    Add create_evidence with evidence_type as Implementation and description as "Bias mitigation safeguards present" and quality as 0.6 to fairness_evidence If has_bias_safeguards is false:
    Add create_compliance_gap with description as "No bias mitigation safeguards identified" and severity as Medium____ to fairness_gaps Let result be if Collections.List.is_empty with lst as fairness_gaps then Compliant__ else Partially_Compliant Return DetailedCheckResult with:
    result as result
    evidence as fairness_evidence
    gaps as fairness_gaps
    confidence as 0.6

Process called "evaluate_transparency_principle" that takes principle as ConstitutionalPrinciple and system as SystemSpecification returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Let transparency_evidence be list containing
    Let transparency_gaps be list containing Note: Check explanation capability
    If system.decision_making.explanation_capability.explanation_quality is Advanced__ or system.decision_making.explanation_capability.explanation_quality is Expert_:
    Add create_evidence with evidence_type as Implementation and description as "Advanced explanation capabilities" and quality as 0.9 to transparency_evidence
    Else if system.decision_making.explanation_capability.explanation_quality is Basic__:
    Add create_compliance_gap with description as "Limited explanation capabilities" and severity as Medium____ to transparency_gaps Let result be if Collections.List.is_empty with lst as transparency_gaps then Compliant__ else Partially_Compliant Return DetailedCheckResult with:
    result as result
    evidence as transparency_evidence
    gaps as transparency_gaps
    confidence as 0.8

Process called "evaluate_accountability_principle" that takes principle as ConstitutionalPrinciple and system as SystemSpecification returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Let accountability_evidence be list containing
    Let accountability_gaps be list containing Note: Check human involvement level
    If system.human_oversight.oversight_level is Continuous_Human_Control or system.human_oversight.oversight_level is Meaningful_Human_Control:
    Add create_evidence with evidence_type as Implementation and description as "Strong human accountability mechanisms" and quality as 0.9 to accountability_evidence
    Else if system.human_oversight.oversight_level is Human_Out_Of_The_Loop:
    Add create_compliance_gap with description as "Insufficient human accountability" and severity as High____ to accountability_gaps Let result be if Collections.List.is_empty with lst as accountability_gaps then Compliant__ else Non_Compliant Return DetailedCheckResult with:
    result as result
    evidence as accountability_evidence
    gaps as accountability_gaps
    confidence as 0.9

Process called "evaluate_article_against_system" that takes article as ConstitutionalArticle and system as SystemSpecification returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Note: Simplified article evaluation
    Return create_default_check_result with result as Compliant__

Process called "create_default_check_result" that takes result as CheckResult returns DetailedCheckResult:
    Return DetailedCheckResult with:
    result as result
    evidence as list containing
    gaps as list containing
    confidence as 0.5

Process called "create_evidence" that takes evidence_type as EvidenceType_ and description as String and quality as Float returns Evidence:
    Return Evidence with:
    evidence_id as generate_unique_id with prefix as "EVID"
    evidence_type as evidence_type
    description as description
    source as "System Specification"
    quality_rating as quality
    verification_status as Verified_

Process called "create_compliance_gap" that takes description as String and severity as GapSeverity returns ComplianceGap:
    Return ComplianceGap with:
    gap_id as generate_unique_id with prefix as "GAP"
    description as description
    severity as severity
    impact as "Potential constitutional non-compliance"
    recommended_actions as list containing "Implement additional safeguards", "Enhance oversight mechanisms"

Process called "calculate_overall_compliance" that takes checks as List[ComplianceCheck] returns OverallComplianceResult:
    Let total_checks be Collections.List.length with lst as checks
    Let compliant_checks be 0
    Let partial_checks be 0 For each check in checks:
    If check.check_result is Compliant__:
    Set compliant_checks to compliant_checks 1
    Else if check.check_result is Partially_Compliant:
    Set partial_checks to partial_checks 1 Let compliance_score be (compliant_checks (partial_checks multiplied by 0.5)) divided by total_checks Let compliance_level be if compliance_score is greater than or equal to 0.95:
    Full_Compliance
    else if compliance_score is greater than or equal to 0.80:
    Substantial_Compliance
    else if compliance_score is greater than or equal to 0.60:
    Partial_Compliance
    else if compliance_score is greater than or equal to 0.40:
    Minimal_Compliance
    else:
    Non_Compliance Return OverallComplianceResult with:
    level as compliance_level
    score as compliance_score

Type called "OverallComplianceResult":
    level as ComplianceLevel_
    score as Float

Process called "extract_violations" that takes checks as List[ComplianceCheck] returns List[ComplianceViolation_]:
    Let violations be list containing For each check in checks:
    If check.check_result is Non_Compliant:
    For each gap in check.gaps:
    If gap.severity is Critical____ or gap.severity is High____:
    Add create_compliance_violation with gap as gap and check as check to violations Return violations

Process called "create_compliance_violation" that takes gap as ComplianceGap and check as ComplianceCheck returns ComplianceViolation_:
    Return ComplianceViolation_ with:
    violation_id as generate_unique_id with prefix as "VIO"
    principle_id as check.requirement_id
    article_id as ""
    violation_type as TechnicalViolation
    severity as map_gap_to_violation_severity with gap_severity as gap.severity
    description as gap.description
    evidence as check.evidence
    remediation_required as true
    deadline as DateTime.add_days with datetime as DateTime.now() and days as 30

Process called "map_gap_to_violation_severity" that takes gap_severity as GapSeverity returns ViolationSeverity__:
    Match gap_severity:
    When Critical____:
    Return Critical_____
    When High____:
    Return Major____
    When Medium____:
    Return Minor____
    When Low____:
    Return Technical
    Otherwise:
    Return Technical

Process called "generate_recommendations" that takes checks as List[ComplianceCheck] returns List[ComplianceRecommendation]:
    Let recommendations be list containing For each check in checks:
    For each gap in check.gaps:
    For each action in gap.recommended_actions:
    Add create_compliance_recommendation with action as action and gap as gap to recommendations Return recommendations

Process called "create_compliance_recommendation" that takes action as String and gap as ComplianceGap returns ComplianceRecommendation:
    Return ComplianceRecommendation with:
    recommendation_id as generate_unique_id with prefix as "REC"
    category as Technical__
    priority as map_gap_to_recommendation_priority with gap_severity as gap.severity
    description as action
    implementation_effort as Medium______
    expected_impact as "Improved constitutional compliance"
    dependencies as list containing

Process called "map_gap_to_recommendation_priority" that takes gap_severity as GapSeverity returns RecommendationPriority:
    Match gap_severity:
    When Critical____:
    Return Immediate
    When High____:
    Return High_____
    When Medium____:
    Return Medium_____
    When Low____:
    Return Low_____
    Otherwise:
    Return Low_____